The paper proposes a new computational framework for structural topology optimization that integrates size, shape, and topology optimization seamlessly in CAD modeling systems. This suggests that the paper may belong to the computer graphics (cs.GR) or computer-aided design (cs.CE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with optimization methods for structural design, which could also place it in the mechanical engineering (cs.ME) or numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. Finally, the paper explicitly mentions CAD modeling systems, which further supports the possibility of it belonging to the computer-aided design sub-category (cs.CAD).
